{
  "texts": [
    "Related to Homomorphic Encryption (HE) and in addition to the TF Encrypted (TF-Encrypted 2023) presented in Sect. 3.2.1, there are other cryptography libraries that implement techniques for HE or other cryptographic protocols.",
    "Other notable HE libraries in the FL context (from Table 7) are presented as follows.",
    "• SEAL (SEAL 2023): Microsoft SEAL is an easy-to-use open-source (MIT licensed) HE library developed by the Cryptography and Privacy Research Group at Microsoft.",
    "The library is written in C++ and is easy to compile and run in many different environments.",
    "The TenSeal (TenSEAL 2023) library from OpenMined which was exposed in Sect. 3.2.2 is built on SEAL."
  ]
}